div.div:
Cross-graph metrics
These are all graphs that connect uncertainties, with trivially inferrable insight connections (connections missed by the graph as it's not built-in to the graph) in dotted lines.
The differences in connections between the same structures (like volatility/variation) on these graphs can act like definitions. (Volatility is 'whatever is one step away from variation on a specific graph' for example).
Using these graphs as a default basis for interface queries enables metrics like 'cross-graph accuracy/similarity/connectivity' to be applied in queries.
